## Context

Toast is a small notification that appears in the corner of our application.

## Rules

There are 2 kinds of toast triggers:

* [server-toast.tsx](mdc:src/lib/server-toast.tsx) for server-side toasts
* `toast` for client-side toasts 

### Client Toast

```tsx
"use client"

import { toast } from "sonner";

function MyComponent() {
  <button onClick={() => toast("Hello")}>Hello</button>
}
```

### Server Toast

* Only available in API routes or server actions

```tsx
import { serverToast } from "@/lib/server-toast";

export const updateProject = orgAction
  .metadata({
    permissions: {
      project: ["update"],
    },
  })
  .inputSchema(updateProjectSchema)
  .action(async ({ parsedInput: input, ctx }) => {
    serverToast("Hello", "error");
  });
```
